    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 26, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🏙️ Kyiv gets the evacuation memo again\n\nMoscow has discovered the one thing more ominous than bombing Kyiv: warning everyone first, then calling it restraint's cousin.\n\n- **The attack:** Ukraine's air force said Russia fired more than 100 drones and two ballistic missiles overnight into Tuesday.\n- **The warning:** Russia urged foreign citizens and diplomatic missions to leave Kyiv, while Sergey Lavrov told Marco Rubio the U.S. should evacuate its embassy staff.\n- **The backdrop:** The alert followed Sunday's mass strike, when Ukraine said Russia used an Oreshnik missile, 600 drones and 90 missiles, killing at least two and wounding 83.\n\n*Diplomacy now comes with a packing list and incoming air alerts.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/2abde640e27e7b320715d74358ba28f3) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/998aeaab5833ca397290d9ee2737b0e5)\n\n---\n\n## 🌊 Lebanon's ceasefire finds the Litani\n\nThe U.S.-brokered ceasefire is holding in the technical sense that everyone can still name it while expanding the war.\n\n- **The line:** AP says Israeli troops clashed with Hezbollah along the Litani River as Israel pushed farther north in southern Lebanon.\n- **The volume:** Reuters reported more than 120 Israeli airstrikes on Tuesday, one of the heaviest days of bombing in weeks.\n- **The toll:** Lebanese health officials put the cumulative offensive since March 2 at 3,213 dead and 9,737 wounded as Netanyahu said Israel would deepen operations.\n\n*The ceasefire has become less a stop sign than a geographic suggestion.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/032806ee1d45539b9cffc92b6e61ad56) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/israel-expands-ground-operation-beyond-yellow-line-in-south-lebanon-as-clashes-intensify-4710390)\n\n---\n\n## 📴 Iran reopens the window, maybe\n\nTehran's internet blackout is ending the way many wars negotiate peace: with one office opening the door and another trying to nail it shut.\n\n- **The order:** Iranian state media said President Masoud Pezeshkian ordered international internet access restored after an 87-day blackout tied to the war.\n- **The counterweight:** AFP reported Iran's judiciary suspended the presidential body that ordered restoration, leaving the reopening partial and politically contested.\n- **The war file:** Iran also denounced Monday's U.S. strikes as bad faith, while Washington said the targets included missile launch sites and boats laying mines.\n\n*Connectivity is back just enough to watch the power struggle load slowly.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/47980a4d87c63c0adb873d306f9b932c) | [Reuters via MarketScreener](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/iran-s-president-orders-reopening-of-international-internet-access-state-media-reports-ce7f5adddb8af222) | [AFP via Dawn](https://www.dawn.com/news/amp/2003264)"
  }
]
